([Faizan Shahzad Khan]) (Aslam Rana) (Obaid Khan) ([[Tariq Butt]]) (Shearaz Hassan) (Shahid 612) (Masoodi) (Hafees Ali)\n* 2012 (Maqsood Hassan) (Agha Shearaz) (Hafees Ali) ([Faizan Shahzad Khan])  (Irfan Motiwala) (Qasim Latif) (Ilyas Nadeem) (Nasir Sharif) (Khawaja Saleem) ([[Ashraf Khan]])\n* 2013 (Mohoroom Ramzan) (Ilyas Nadeem) ([[Ismil Tara]]) ([[Ayaz Khan]]) ([[Fazal Baltistani]]) ([Faizan Shahzad Khan]) (Maqsoood Hassan)  (Hafeez Ali) (Obaid Khan) (Nasir Sharif) ([[Manzoor Quearashi]])\n* 2014  ([Faizan Shahzad Khan])(Shahid 612) (Shahbab Khan) (Haneef Bachan) (Nasir Sharif) (Hafeez ali) (Urooj Aabas) ([[Ayaz Khan]]) ([[Manzoor Quearashi]]) (Arif Siddiqi) (Bahadur Sheikh) (Fazal Baltistani) (Mehboob Sultan) (Waseem Dhamia)\n* 2015 ([Faizan Shahzad Khan]) (Umair Laghari) (Fazal Baltistani) (Ghulaam Mehdi) (Nasir Sharif) (Arif Siddiqi) (Akbar Khan) (Shahbab Khan) (Irfan Motiwala) (Urooj Aabas) (Hafeez Ali)\n* 2016 ([[Naveed Raza]]) (Haneef Bachan) (Irfan Motiwala) ([[Ayaz Khan]]) (Khawaja Saleem) (Fazal Baltistani) ([[Zufliqar Sheikh]]) (Ayaz Khan) (Arif Siddiqi)\n* 2017 ([[Dodi Khan]]) ([[Ayaz Khan]]) (Nasir Sharif) (Tariq Butt) (Shahbab Khan) (Shahid 612) (Arif Siddiqi) (Urooj Abas) (Khawaja Akmal) (Akbar Khan)\n\n===By occupation===\n*Plumber : [[Hafeez Ali]] (2009) episode 3 [[Saleem Mairaj]] (2013) episode 239\n* Faizi Sun Jaggu dada Punter : [[Faizan Shahzad Khan]] (2015) episode 274 - 297\n*Nabeel's girlfriends: [[Nousheen Shah]] (2009) episode 5 [[Javeria Abbasi]] (2009) episode 10 [[Nashata Ali]] (2010) ep 18 [[Sara]]{{dn|date=April 2020}} (2010) ep 40 [[Amber Khan]] (2011) ep 71 [[Aysha]] (2011) ep 85 [[Mahjabeen Habib]] (2011) [[Jahan Aara]] (2012) [[Sonia Rao]] (2013) [[Anum Aqeel]] (2015)\n<!--==Copyright issues==\nNabeel Zafar, the producer of Bulbulay, joined BOL TV as its CEO few years back and decided that he would bring Bulbulay to BOL. Although rights had been acquired by ARY. However, Nabeel then resigned after a dispute with BOL and there were no further talks of shifting Bulbulay from ARY to BOL. After BOL started airing Phir Bulbulay, ARY filed a lawsuit against them for airing the show illegally. Finally, the court issued a stay order against BOL TV and restricted them from airing the sitcom on the channel.-->\n\n<!--==Bol Entertainment==\nOn 7 May 2019, Bulbulay releases its second season, titled \"Phir Bulbulay\", after a gap of 2 years on the [[BOL Network]] entertainment channel \"BOL Entertainment\".-->\n\n<!--==Assistant directors==\n* [[Zahid Ali Balti]] (2009-2010)Ep 1-37\n* [[Faizan Shahzad Khan]] (2010) episode 36-39  \n* [[Vickey]] (2010) episode 40-53\n* [[Waqas Javed]] (2010-2011) episode 54-83\n* [[Nasir Sharif]] (2015)\n* [[Faizan Shahzad Khan]] as associate/casting director (2011-2015) episode 88-361-->\n\n==Reception==\n''Bulbulay'' achieved the highest-ever rating of a Pakistani comedy series, with a rating of 8.0 TRPs (Television Rating Points), which is more than any other Pakistani comedy drama. It has a current rating of 7.8/10 on [[IMDb]]. ''Bulbulay'' also won the \"Best Sitcom\" award for three consecutive years, from 2010 to 2012, at the [[Pakistan Media Awards]].\n\nDue to its popularity, the series is shown in other countries,<ref>{{cite news|title=Digital Dreams|url=http://www.kashmirlife.net/digital-dreams-vol06-issue09-58995/ |accessdate=30 December 2014|work=Kashmir Life}}</ref> including the UK; and soon it will be aired in India on the [[Zee Zindagi]] channel.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of programs broadcast by ARY Digital]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title | 4191600 }}\n* [http://rava.pk/ary-digital/bulbulay/ Watch All Episodes of Bulbulay]\n* {{facebook|BulbulayonARYDigital}}\n{{ARY Digital Programs}}\n\n[[Category:Pakistani television sitcoms]]\n[[Category:Pakistani drama television series]]\n[[Category:Comedy-drama television series]]\n[[Category:Urdu-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Karachi]]\n[[Category:ARY Digital television series]]\n[[Category:2009 Pakistani television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2000s Pakistani television series]]\n[[Category:2010s Pakistani television series]]\n", "name_user": "Y71-H63", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eEpisode 83-87 (Bubulay in Dubai)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bulbulay"}
{"title_page": "Nova Scotia killings", "text_new": "{{pp-move-dispute|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Series of shootings in Nova Scotia, Canada}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Current|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use Canadian English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox civilian attack\n| title            = Nova Scotia killings\n{{OSM Location map\n| coord            = {{coord|45.1965|-63.3377}}\n|  zoom            = 7\n| float            = center\n| width            = 300\n| height           = 206\n| caption          =\n|   title          =\n|    minimap       = file\n|  mini-file       = Canada_location_map.svg\n| mini-width       = 120\n|mini-height       = 64\n|  minipog-x       = 105\n|  minipog-y       = 48\n|  scalemark       = 120 <!-- shifts the scalemark further to the left -->\n|      shape1      = image\n|       mark1      = Red pog.svg\n|      label1      = Portapique, Nova Scotia\n| mark-coord1      = {{coord|45.4015|-63.6977}} \n|  label-pos1      = bottom\n| label-size1      = 10\n|label-color1      = black\n| label-offset-x1  =\n| label-offset-y1  =\n|mark-title1       = Portapique, NS\n|mark-image1       =\n|mark-description1 =\n|      label2      = Enfield, Nova Scotia\n|       mark2      = Red pog.svg\n| mark-size2       = 8\n|  label-pos2      = left\n| label-size2      = 10\n|label-color2      = black\n| mark-coord2      = {{coord|44.9274|-63.5366}}\n|mark-title2       = Enfield, NS\n}}\n| partof           = \n| image            = \n| image_size       = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| map              = \n| map_size         = \n| map_alt          = \n| map_caption      = Portapique in Nova Scotia\n| susperp          = \n| location         = [[Nova Scotia]], Canada\n| target           = \n| date             = {{start date|2020|4|18}} \u2013<br>{{end date|2020|4|19}}\n| time             = \n| timezone         = [[UTC\u221203:00]]\n| coordinates      = \n| type             = [[Spree shooting]], [[arson]], [[mass murder]]\n| weapons          = Firearm, fires\n| fatalities       = At least 17 (including the perpetrator)\n| injuries         = At least 2\n| victim           = \n| perp             = Gabriel Wortman<ref name=\"CBC\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/rcmp-weapon-lockdown-portapique-1.5537598|title=RCMP officer among 17 confirmed dead in Nova Scotia killing spree|publisher=CBC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419130936/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/rcmp-weapon-lockdown-portapique-1.5537598|archive-date=April 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| numparts         = \n| numpart          = \n| dfens            = \n| dfen             = \n| footage          = \n| motive           = \n}}\n\nA [[spree killing]] comprising shootings and arson took place in the northern part of the [[Canada|Canadian]] province of [[Nova Scotia]], between April 18 and 19, 2020. A man identified as 51-year-old Gabriel Wortman killed at least 16 people, including a [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police]] (RCMP) officer, and injured at least two others before being killed by police following a car chase.<ref name=\"CBC\" /><ref name=nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman>{{Cite news|title=At Least 16 Killed in Nova Scotia Shooting, Police Say|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/19/world/canada/nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman.html|last=Diaz|first=Johnny|date=April 19, 2020|access-date=April 19, 2020|last2=Bilefsky|first2=Dan|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419142013/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/19/world/canada/nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman.html|archive-date=April 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Politico\">{{cite news|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/04/19/at-least-10-dead-in-canadian-shooting-rampage-195506|title=Gunman kills at least 16, including officer, in Nova Scotia|last=Blatchford|first=Andy|publisher=Politico|accessdate=April 20, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref> It is the deadliest attack of its kind in Canadian history.<ref name=\"AP\">{{cite news|url=https://apnews.com/7c9a33ae52420e0ddbfb5275898a7e79|title=16 killed in shooting rampage, deadliest in Canadian history|last=Gillies|first=Rob|publisher=Associated Press|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419202425/https://apnews.com/7c9a33ae52420e0ddbfb5275898a7e79|archive-date=April 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Police say no motive has been established yet.<ref name=\"nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman\" />\n\n==Killings==\nAt 11:32 p.m. on April 18,<ref name=\"CBC\" /> police responded to multiple [[9-1-1]] calls regarding a gun-related incident in the small community of [[Portapique]], {{convert|130|km|mi}} north of [[Halifax, Nova Scotia|Halifax]].<ref name=nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman/><ref name=\"CBC2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/nova-scotia-timeline-active-shooter-portapique-1.5537756|title=Timeline: How an active-shooter situation unfolded in Nova Scotia|publisher=CBC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420001136/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/nova-scotia-timeline-active-shooter-portapique-1.5537756|archive-date=April 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"NBC\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/canadian-authorities-say-mass-shooting-suspect-may-have-been-disguised-n1187381|title=16 dead, including officer, in shooting, Canadian authorities say|last1=Madani|first1=Doha|last2=Stelloh|first2=Tim|publisher=NBC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"CBC3\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/mass-killings-what-we-know-what-we-don-t-1.5537918|title=Nova Scotia mass killings: What we know and what we don't know|publisher=CBC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420034520/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/mass-killings-what-we-know-what-we-don-t-1.5537918|archive-date=April 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> They found several dead and injured inside and outside a home, but not the suspect.<ref name=\"ABC\">{{cite news|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/multiple-victims-canada-shooting-suspect-dressed-police-officer/story?id=70232582|title=16 dead, including police officer, in deadliest shooting in Canadian history|last=Deliso|first=Meredith|publisher=ABC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe investigation overnight led police to many crime scenes that were scattered over at least {{convert|50|km|mi}}.<ref name=\"CBC3\" /> At around 8:00 a.m. on April 19, police announced that they were dealing with an [[active shooter]] situation. Residents were advised by the RCMP to stay indoors, while a portion of the town was evacuated.<ref name=nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman/><ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"MassLive\">{{cite news|url=https://www.masslive.com/news/2020/04/nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman-kills-16-including-police-officer-in-canadas-deadliest-shooting-attack.html|title=Nova Scotia shooting: Gabriel Wortman kills 16 including police officer in Canada's deadliest shooting attack|publisher=MassLive|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref> Three buildings and two cars were reported burning, which required a firefighter response.<ref name=\"CBC\" /><ref name=nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman/><ref name=\"CTV\">{{cite news|url=https://atlantic.ctvnews.ca/nova-scotia-shooting-suspect-shot-and-killed-by-police-1.4902687|title=At least 17 people killed in N.S. shooting; deadliest such attack in Canada: police|last=Jerrett|first=Andrea|publisher=CTV News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\nGabriel Wortman, age 51, was identified as the shooter at 8:54 a.m. on April 19.<ref name=\"CBC\" /> Between 10:04 and 11:24, Wortman was sighted in [[Debert]], [[Brookfield, Nova Scotia|Brookfield]], and [[Milford (Halifax), Nova Scotia|Milford]].<ref name=\"CBC\" /><ref name=\"CTV\" /> In the same time-frame, the public was warned that he might be [[police impersonation|posing as an RCMP officer]] and operating a vehicle made to look like an RCMP cruiser,<ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"CTV\" /><ref>{{cite news|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6840120/nova-scotia-shooting-timeline/|title=Timeline of what we know about Nova Scotia killing spree that left RCMP officer, 16 others dead|publisher=Global News|last=Shah|first=Maryam|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref> and that he was travelling on Highway 4 near [[Glenholme]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/a-timeline-of-the-deadly-shooting-incident-in-nova-scotia-1.4902954|title=A timeline of the deadly shooting incident in Nova Scotia|last=Lopez-Martinez|first=Melissa|date=April 19, 2020|website=CTV News|language=en|access-date=April 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420053707/https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/a-timeline-of-the-deadly-shooting-incident-in-nova-scotia-1.4902954|archive-date=April 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Residents were urged to avoid the area.<ref name=global-news-rcmp-active-shooter-portapique-n-s>{{Cite news|title=17 dead, including one RCMP officer, after shooting spree in Portapique, N.S.|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6838880/rcmp-active-shooter-portapique-n-s/|last=Quon|first=Alexander|date=April 19, 2020|access-date=April 19, 2020|publisher=[[Global News]]|last2=Stephenson|first2=Mercedes|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419202613/https://globalnews.ca/news/6838880/rcmp-active-shooter-portapique-n-s/|archive-date=April 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Police asked the public to call 9-1-1 immediately if they spotted the vehicle.<ref name=\"ABC\" /> Another hour later, they said he switched to a silver [[Chevrolet Tracker (Americas)|Chevrolet Tracker]] [[sports utility vehicle]].<ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"BBC\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52346447|title=Canada shooting: Gunman kills at least 16 in rural Canada|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419211041/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52346447|archive-date=April 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nNearly twelve hours after police first received the firearms complaint,<ref name=\"Vox\">{{cite news|url=https://www.vox.com/world/2020/4/19/21227349/mass-shooting-nova-scotia-canada-enfield-portapique|title=What we know about a mass shooting in Nova Scotia, Canada|publisher=Vox|last=Collins|first=Sean|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref> Wortman was killed by police outside a gas station restaurant at the [[Irving Oil]] Big Stop in [[Enfield, Nova Scotia|Enfield]], about {{convert|92|km|mi}} south of Portapique and about {{convert|40|km|mi}} north of Halifax.<ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"CTV\" /> The [[Serious Incident Response Team]] announced it would be conducting an investigation into the officer-involved shooting.<ref name=\"CBC\" />\n\n==Perpetrator==\nThe shooter was identified as 51-year-old Gabriel Wortman, a [[denturist]] working in the Halifax area. He owned real estate in Portapique and [[Dartmouth, Nova Scotia|Dartmouth]].<ref name=\"CBC\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/20/nova-scotia-shooting-gunman-profile-quiet-gentle-denturist|title=Nova Scotia shooting: shock and surprise at killings by denturist|first=Leyland|last=Cecco|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|website=The Guardian}}</ref> He attended [[Riverview High School (New Brunswick)|Riverview High School]] in New Brunswick and aspired to be a police officer.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://atlantic.ctvnews.ca/just-unbelievable-neighbours-of-nova-scotia-shooting-suspect-shocked-by-news-1.4903021|title='Just unbelievable': Neighbours of Nova Scotia shooting suspect shocked by news|date=2020-04-19|website=Atlantic|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> Wortman was shown to have had a degree of obsession for policing, having a hobby of buying law enforcement memorabilia and refurbishing old police cruisers. One person called Wortman's home a \"shrine\" for the RCMP.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/canada/article-nova-scotia-mass-shooter-was-a-denturist-with-an-obsession-for/|title=Nova Scotia mass shooter was a denturist with an obsession for policing|publisher=The Globe and Mail|last1=Woo|first1=Andrew|last2=Mercer|first2=Greg|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420055810/https://www.theglobeandmail.com/canada/article-nova-scotia-mass-shooter-was-a-denturist-with-an-obsession-for/|archive-date=April 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He stored the two police cruisers he bought near his dental clinic.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nNo motive has been established for the killings, and it is not considered by authorities to be an act of [[terrorism]].<ref name=\"nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman\" /> However, neighbors said Wortman struggled with alcoholism, and his business, which he made a lot of money from, was adversely impacted by the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Nova Scotia|coronavirus pandemic]] forcing the shuttering of all non-essential dental services.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Victims==\nAt least 17 people were killed, one of them a 23-year veteran RCMP officer, Constable Heidi Stevenson. A second RCMP officer was injured and is in stable condition.<ref name=\"CBC\" /><ref name=global-news-rcmp-active-shooter-portapique-n-s /> At least one other person was also injured.<ref name=\"CBC\" /> According to Commissioner [[Brenda Lucki]], some of the first victims had connections to Wortman, but as the killings continued, the targets became more random.<ref name=nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman/> The victims are believed to have died from gunshot wounds, but other causes are also being investigated.<ref name=\"BBC-52346447\">{{cite web |title=Gunman kills at least 16 in rural Canada |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-52346447 |website=BBC News |accessdate=20 April 2020 |date=20 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420075915/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-52346447 |archive-date=April 20, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"CBC3\" />\n\n==Reactions==\nNova Scotia Premier [[Stephen McNeil]] told reporters, \"This is one of the most senseless acts of violence in our province's history.\" He expressed his condolences to the residents affected and the families of the victims.<ref name=\"CTV2\">{{cite news|url=https://atlantic.ctvnews.ca/shooting-one-of-the-most-senseless-acts-of-violence-in-nova-scotia-s-history-premier-1.4902917|title=Shooting 'one of the most senseless acts of violence' in Nova Scotia's history: premier|last=Jerrett|first=Andrea|publisher=CTV News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref> Prime Minister [[Justin Trudeau]] also expressed his condolences.<ref name=\"CBC\" />\n\n==See also==\n* [[\u00c9cole Polytechnique massacre]]\n* [[Moncton shooting]]\n* [[List of massacres in Canada]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2020 crimes in Canada]]\n[[Category:2020 in Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:2020 mass shootings]]\n[[Category:2020 mass shootings in North America]]\n[[Category:2020 murders in North America]]\n[[Category:2020s mass shootings in North America]]\n[[Category:April 2020 crimes]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in Canada]]\n[[Category:Arson in Canada]]\n[[Category:Arson in the 2020s]]\n[[Category:Attacks in 2020]]\n[[Category:Crime in Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:Death in Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:Deaths by firearm in Canada]]\n[[Category:Mass shootings in Canada]]\n[[Category:Royal Canadian Mounted Police]]\n[[Category:Spree shootings in Canada]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-move-dispute|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Series of shootings in Nova Scotia, Canada}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Current|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use Canadian English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox civilian attack\n| title            = Nova Scotia killings\n{{OSM Location map\n| coord            = {{coord|45.1965|-63.3377}}\n|  zoom            = 7\n| float            = center\n| width            = 300\n| height           = 206\n| caption          =\n|   title          =\n|    minimap       = file\n|  mini-file       = Canada_location_map.svg\n| mini-width       = 120\n|mini-height       = 64\n|  minipog-x       = 105\n|  minipog-y       = 48\n|  scalemark       = 120 <!-- shifts the scalemark further to the left -->\n|      shape1      = image\n|       mark1      = Red pog.svg\n|      label1      = Portapique, Nova Scotia\n| mark-coord1      = {{coord|45.4015|-63.6977}} \n|  label-pos1      = bottom\n| label-size1      = 10\n|label-color1      = black\n| label-offset-x1  =\n| label-offset-y1  =\n|mark-title1       = Portapique, NS\n|mark-image1       =\n|mark-description1 =\n|      label2      = Enfield, Nova Scotia\n|       mark2      = Red pog.svg\n| mark-size2       = 8\n|  label-pos2      = left\n| label-size2      = 10\n|label-color2      = black\n| mark-coord2      = {{coord|44.9274|-63.5366}}\n|mark-title2       = Enfield, NS\n}}\n| partof           = \n| image            = \n| image_size       = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| map              = \n| map_size         = \n| map_alt          = \n| map_caption      = Portapique in Nova Scotia\n| susperp          = \n| location         = [[Nova Scotia]], Canada\n| target           = \n| date             = {{start date|2020|4|18}} \u2013<br>{{end date|2020|4|19}}\n| time             = \n| timezone         = [[UTC\u221203:00]]\n| coordinates      = \n| type             = [[Spree shooting]], [[arson]], [[mass murder]]\n| weapons          = Firearm, fires\n| fatalities       = At least 17 (including the perpetrator)\n| injuries         = At least 2\n| victim           = \n| perp             = Gabriel Wortman<ref name=\"CBC\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/rcmp-weapon-lockdown-portapique-1.5537598|title=RCMP officer among 17 confirmed dead in Nova Scotia killing spree|publisher=CBC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419130936/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/rcmp-weapon-lockdown-portapique-1.5537598|archive-date=April 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| numparts         = \n| numpart          = \n| dfens            = \n| dfen             = \n| footage          = \n| motive           = \n}}\n\nA [[spree killing]] comprising shootings and arson took place in the northern part of the [[Canada|Canadian]] province of [[Nova Scotia]], between April 18 and 19, 2020. A man identified as 51-year-old Gabriel Wortman killed at least 16 people, including a [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police]] (RCMP) officer, and injured at least two others before being killed by police following a car chase.<ref name=\"CBC\" /><ref name=nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman>{{Cite news|title=At Least 16 Killed in Nova Scotia Shooting, Police Say|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/19/world/canada/nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman.html|last=Diaz|first=Johnny|date=April 19, 2020|access-date=April 19, 2020|last2=Bilefsky|first2=Dan|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419142013/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/19/world/canada/nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman.html|archive-date=April 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Politico\">{{cite news|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/04/19/at-least-10-dead-in-canadian-shooting-rampage-195506|title=Gunman kills at least 16, including officer, in Nova Scotia|last=Blatchford|first=Andy|publisher=Politico|accessdate=April 20, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref> It is the deadliest attack of its kind in Canadian history.<ref name=\"AP\">{{cite news|url=https://apnews.com/7c9a33ae52420e0ddbfb5275898a7e79|title=16 killed in shooting rampage, deadliest in Canadian history|last=Gillies|first=Rob|publisher=Associated Press|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419202425/https://apnews.com/7c9a33ae52420e0ddbfb5275898a7e79|archive-date=April 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Police say no motive has been established yet.<ref name=\"nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman\" />\n\n==Killings==\nAt 11:32 p.m. on April 18,<ref name=\"CBC\" /> police responded to multiple [[9-1-1]] calls regarding a gun-related incident in the small community of [[Portapique]], {{convert|130|km|mi}} north of [[Halifax, Nova Scotia|Halifax]].<ref name=nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman/><ref name=\"CBC2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/nova-scotia-timeline-active-shooter-portapique-1.5537756|title=Timeline: How an active-shooter situation unfolded in Nova Scotia|publisher=CBC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420001136/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/nova-scotia-timeline-active-shooter-portapique-1.5537756|archive-date=April 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"NBC\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/canadian-authorities-say-mass-shooting-suspect-may-have-been-disguised-n1187381|title=16 dead, including officer, in shooting, Canadian authorities say|last1=Madani|first1=Doha|last2=Stelloh|first2=Tim|publisher=NBC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"CBC3\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/mass-killings-what-we-know-what-we-don-t-1.5537918|title=Nova Scotia mass killings: What we know and what we don't know|publisher=CBC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420034520/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/mass-killings-what-we-know-what-we-don-t-1.5537918|archive-date=April 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> They found several dead and injured inside and outside a home, but not the suspect.<ref name=\"ABC\">{{cite news|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/multiple-victims-canada-shooting-suspect-dressed-police-officer/story?id=70232582|title=16 dead, including police officer, in deadliest shooting in Canadian history|last=Deliso|first=Meredith|publisher=ABC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe investigation overnight led police to many crime scenes that were scattered over at least {{convert|50|km|mi}}.<ref name=\"CBC3\" /> At around 8:00 a.m. on April 19, police announced that they were dealing with an [[active shooter]] situation. Residents were advised by the RCMP to stay indoors, while a portion of the town was evacuated.<ref name=nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman/><ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"MassLive\">{{cite news|url=https://www.masslive.com/news/2020/04/nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman-kills-16-including-police-officer-in-canadas-deadliest-shooting-attack.html|title=Nova Scotia shooting: Gabriel Wortman kills 16 including police officer in Canada's deadliest shooting attack|publisher=MassLive|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref> Three buildings and two cars were reported burning, which required a firefighter response.<ref name=\"CBC\" /><ref name=nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman/><ref name=\"CTV\">{{cite news|url=https://atlantic.ctvnews.ca/nova-scotia-shooting-suspect-shot-and-killed-by-police-1.4902687|title=At least 17 people killed in N.S. shooting; deadliest such attack in Canada: police|last=Jerrett|first=Andrea|publisher=CTV News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\nGabriel Wortman, age 51, was identified as the shooter at 8:54 a.m. on April 19.<ref name=\"CBC\" /> Between 10:04 and 11:24, Wortman was sighted in [[Debert]], [[Brookfield, Nova Scotia|Brookfield]], and [[Milford (Halifax), Nova Scotia|Milford]].<ref name=\"CBC\" /><ref name=\"CTV\" /> In the same time-frame, the public was warned that he may be [[police impersonation|posing as an RCMP officer]] and operating a vehicle made to look like an RCMP cruiser,<ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"CTV\" /><ref>{{cite news|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6840120/nova-scotia-shooting-timeline/|title=Timeline of what we know about Nova Scotia killing spree that left RCMP officer, 16 others dead|publisher=Global News|last=Shah|first=Maryam|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref> and that he was travelling on Highway 4 near [[Glenholme]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/a-timeline-of-the-deadly-shooting-incident-in-nova-scotia-1.4902954|title=A timeline of the deadly shooting incident in Nova Scotia|last=Lopez-Martinez|first=Melissa|date=April 19, 2020|website=CTV News|language=en|access-date=April 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420053707/https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/a-timeline-of-the-deadly-shooting-incident-in-nova-scotia-1.4902954|archive-date=April 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Residents were urged to avoid the area.<ref name=global-news-rcmp-active-shooter-portapique-n-s>{{Cite news|title=17 dead, including one RCMP officer, after shooting spree in Portapique, N.S.|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/6838880/rcmp-active-shooter-portapique-n-s/|last=Quon|first=Alexander|date=April 19, 2020|access-date=April 19, 2020|publisher=[[Global News]]|last2=Stephenson|first2=Mercedes|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419202613/https://globalnews.ca/news/6838880/rcmp-active-shooter-portapique-n-s/|archive-date=April 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Police asked the public to call 9-1-1 immediately if they spotted the vehicle.<ref name=\"ABC\" /> Another hour later, they said he switched to a silver [[Chevrolet Tracker (Americas)|Chevrolet Tracker]] [[sports utility vehicle]].<ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"BBC\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52346447|title=Canada shooting: Gunman kills at least 16 in rural Canada|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419211041/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52346447|archive-date=April 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nNearly twelve hours after police first received the firearms complaint,<ref name=\"Vox\">{{cite news|url=https://www.vox.com/world/2020/4/19/21227349/mass-shooting-nova-scotia-canada-enfield-portapique|title=What we know about a mass shooting in Nova Scotia, Canada|publisher=Vox|last=Collins|first=Sean|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref> Wortman was killed by police outside a gas station restaurant at the [[Irving Oil]] Big Stop in [[Enfield, Nova Scotia|Enfield]], about {{convert|92|km|mi}} south of Portapique and about {{convert|40|km|mi}} north of Halifax.<ref name=\"CBC2\" /><ref name=\"CTV\" /> The [[Serious Incident Response Team]] announced it would be conducting an investigation into the officer-involved shooting.<ref name=\"CBC\" />\n\n==Perpetrator==\nThe shooter was identified as 51-year-old Gabriel Wortman, a [[denturist]] working in the Halifax area. He owned real estate in Portapique and [[Dartmouth, Nova Scotia|Dartmouth]].<ref name=\"CBC\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/20/nova-scotia-shooting-gunman-profile-quiet-gentle-denturist|title=Nova Scotia shooting: shock and surprise at killings by denturist|first=Leyland|last=Cecco|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 19, 2020|website=The Guardian}}</ref> He attended [[Riverview High School (New Brunswick)|Riverview High School]] in New Brunswick and aspired to be a police officer.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://atlantic.ctvnews.ca/just-unbelievable-neighbours-of-nova-scotia-shooting-suspect-shocked-by-news-1.4903021|title='Just unbelievable': Neighbours of Nova Scotia shooting suspect shocked by news|date=2020-04-19|website=Atlantic|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> Wortman was shown to have had a degree of obsession for policing, having a hobby of buying law enforcement memorabilia and refurbishing old police cruisers. One person called Wortman's home a \"shrine\" for the RCMP.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/canada/article-nova-scotia-mass-shooter-was-a-denturist-with-an-obsession-for/|title=Nova Scotia mass shooter was a denturist with an obsession for policing|publisher=The Globe and Mail|last1=Woo|first1=Andrew|last2=Mercer|first2=Greg|date=April 19, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420055810/https://www.theglobeandmail.com/canada/article-nova-scotia-mass-shooter-was-a-denturist-with-an-obsession-for/|archive-date=April 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He stored the two police cruisers he bought near his dental clinic.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nNo motive has been established for the killings, and it is not considered by authorities to be an act of [[terrorism]].<ref name=\"nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman\" /> However, neighbors said Wortman struggled with alcoholism, and his business, which he made a lot of money from, was adversely impacted by the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Nova Scotia|coronavirus pandemic]] forcing the shuttering of all non-essential dental services.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Victims==\nAt least 17 people were killed, one of them a 23-year veteran RCMP officer, Constable Heidi Stevenson. A second RCMP officer was injured and is in stable condition.<ref name=\"CBC\" /><ref name=global-news-rcmp-active-shooter-portapique-n-s /> At least one other person was also injured.<ref name=\"CBC\" /> According to Commissioner [[Brenda Lucki]], some of the first victims had connections to Wortman, but as the killings continued, the targets became more random.<ref name=nyt-nova-scotia-shooting-gabriel-wortman/> The victims are believed to have died from gunshot wounds, but other causes are also being investigated.<ref name=\"BBC-52346447\">{{cite web |title=Gunman kills at least 16 in rural Canada |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-52346447 |website=BBC News |accessdate=20 April 2020 |date=20 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200420075915/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-52346447 |archive-date=April 20, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"CBC3\" />\n\n==Reactions==\nNova Scotia Premier [[Stephen McNeil]] told reporters, \"This is one of the most senseless acts of violence in our province's history.\" He expressed his condolences to the residents affected and the families of the victims.<ref name=\"CTV2\">{{cite news|url=https://atlantic.ctvnews.ca/shooting-one-of-the-most-senseless-acts-of-violence-in-nova-scotia-s-history-premier-1.4902917|title=Shooting 'one of the most senseless acts of violence' in Nova Scotia's history: premier|last=Jerrett|first=Andrea|publisher=CTV News|accessdate=April 19, 2020|date=April 19, 2020}}</ref> Prime Minister [[Justin Trudeau]] also expressed his condolences.<ref name=\"CBC\" />\n\n==See also==\n* [[\u00c9cole Polytechnique massacre]]\n* [[Moncton shooting]]\n* [[List of massacres in Canada]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2020 crimes in Canada]]\n[[Category:2020 in Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:2020 mass shootings]]\n[[Category:2020 mass shootings in North America]]\n[[Category:2020 murders in North America]]\n[[Category:2020s mass shootings in North America]]\n[[Category:April 2020 crimes]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in Canada]]\n[[Category:Arson in Canada]]\n[[Category:Arson in the 2020s]]\n[[Category:Attacks in 2020]]\n[[Category:Crime in Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:Death in Nova Scotia]]\n[[Category:Deaths by firearm in Canada]]\n[[Category:Mass shootings in Canada]]\n[[Category:Royal Canadian Mounted Police]]\n[[Category:Spree shootings in Canada]]\n